<DocsLayout title="Terraform — Azure">
  <h1>Terraform — Azure</h1>
  <p>
    The Azure Terraform module deploys EncodeSwarmr into a dedicated resource group with a Linux VM for the
    controller, a Virtual Machine Scale Set for agents, Azure Database for PostgreSQL, Azure Files for shared
    storage, and an Azure Load Balancer.
  </p>

  <h2>Architecture</h2>
  <pre><code>                    ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
                    │         Resource Group                 │
                    │                                        │
                    │  ┌────────────────────────────────┐   │
                    │  │     Virtual Network             │   │
                    │  │     10.0.0.0/16                 │   │
                    │  │                                 │   │
                    │  │  Public Subnet  10.0.1.0/24     │   │
                    │  │  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │   │
                    │  │  │  Azure Load Balancer      │  │   │
                    │  │  │  (HTTP :8080, TCP :9443)  │  │   │
                    │  │  └──────────┬───────────────┘  │   │
                    │  │             │                   │   │
                    │  │  Private Subnet  10.0.2.0/24   │   │
                    │  │  ┌──────────▼──────────────┐   │   │
                    │  │  │  Linux VM: Controller    │   │   │
                    │  │  │  (Standard_D2s_v3)       │   │   │
                    │  │  │  (+ 2nd VM in HA mode)   │   │   │
                    │  │  └──────────┬───────────────┘  │   │
                    │  │             │                   │   │
                    │  │  ┌──────────▼──────────────┐   │   │
                    │  │  │  Azure DB for PostgreSQL │   │   │
                    │  │  │  (Flexible Server)       │   │   │
                    │  │  └─────────────────────────┘   │   │
                    │  │                                 │   │
                    │  │  Agent Subnet  10.0.3.0/24      │   │
                    │  │  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │   │
                    │  │  │  VMSS: Agent Instances   │  │   │
                    │  │  │  (Standard_F8s_v2)       │  │   │
                    │  │  └──────────────────────────┘  │   │
                    │  │                                 │   │
                    │  │  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │   │
                    │  │  │  Azure Files Share        │  │   │
                    │  │  │  (shared media storage)   │  │   │
                    │  │  └──────────────────────────┘  │   │
                    │  └────────────────────────────────┘   │
                    └──────────────────────────────────────┘</code></pre>

  <h2>Standard vs HA Mode</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Standard mode</strong> deploys a single controller VM behind the load balancer with a single-zone
    Flexible PostgreSQL server. This is suitable for development, staging, or workloads that can tolerate brief
    downtime during maintenance.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>HA mode</strong> deploys two controller VMs in separate Availability Zones, a zone-redundant Azure
    Database for PostgreSQL Flexible Server, and cross-zone VMSS agent placement. The load balancer routes HTTP
    and gRPC traffic across both controllers.
  </p>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Terraform 1.6 or later</li>
    <li>Azure CLI installed and authenticated (<code>az login</code>)</li>
    <li>An active Azure subscription</li>
    <li>Contributor role on the subscription or a resource group pre-created with appropriate permissions</li>
    <li>The <code>Microsoft.Compute</code>, <code>Microsoft.Network</code>, <code>Microsoft.DBforPostgreSQL</code>, and <code>Microsoft.Storage</code> resource providers registered in the subscription</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Quick Start</h2>

  <h3>1. Authenticate with Azure</h3>
  <pre><code>az login
az account set --subscription "My Subscription"</code></pre>

  <h3>2. Configure variables</h3>
  <pre><code>cd deploy/terraform/azure
cp terraform.tfvars.example terraform.tfvars
$EDITOR terraform.tfvars</code></pre>

  <pre><code># terraform.tfvars
location             = "eastus"
resource_group_name  = "encodeswarmr-rg"
encodeswarmr_version = "1.2.0"

# Controller
controller_vm_size   = "Standard_D2s_v3"

# Agents
agent_vm_size        = "Standard_F8s_v2"
agent_min_count      = 1
agent_max_count      = 10
agent_desired_count  = 2

# Database
db_sku_name          = "Standard_D2ds_v4"
db_admin_username    = "encodeswarmr"
db_admin_password    = "changeme-use-key-vault"

# Storage
azure_files_quota_gb = 1024

# Optional
# public_ip_domain_label = "encodeswarmr-myco"</code></pre>

  <h3>3. Deploy</h3>
  <pre><code>terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply</code></pre>

  <h3>4. Upload mTLS Certificates</h3>
  <p>After the initial deployment, upload your mTLS certificates to the controller VM:</p>
  <pre><code># Get the controller VM public IP from Terraform outputs
CONTROLLER_IP=$(terraform output -raw controller_public_ip)

# Copy certificates
scp -r certs/ azureuser@$&#123;CONTROLLER_IP&#125;:/etc/encodeswarmr/

# SSH into the controller and restart the service
ssh azureuser@$&#123;CONTROLLER_IP&#125;
sudo systemctl restart encodeswarmr-controller</code></pre>

  <h3>5. Verify</h3>
  <pre><code># Check the load balancer public IP
terraform output load_balancer_ip

# Open the web UI
curl http://$(terraform output -raw load_balancer_ip):8080/health</code></pre>

  <h2>Toggle HA Mode</h2>
  <pre><code># Enable HA — adds a second controller VM and zone-redundant DB
terraform apply -var="ha_enabled=true" -var="controller_count=2" -var="db_zone_redundant=true"

# Disable HA (revert)
terraform apply -var="ha_enabled=false" -var="controller_count=1" -var="db_zone_redundant=false"</code></pre>

  <h2>Cost Estimate</h2>

  <h3>Standard Deployment (East US, approximate)</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Component</th><th>Spec</th><th>Est. Monthly Cost</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Controller VM</td><td>Standard_D2s_v3 (On-Demand)</td><td>~$70</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Agent VMSS</td><td>2 × Standard_F8s_v2</td><td>~$560</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Azure DB PostgreSQL</td><td>Standard_D2ds_v4, 32 GB</td><td>~$105</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Load Balancer</td><td>Standard</td><td>~$20</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Azure Files</td><td>1 TB LRS</td><td>~$55</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Public IPs</td><td>2 static</td><td>~$7</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Data transfer</td><td>variable</td><td>~$20</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td></td><td><strong>~$837/mo</strong></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>HA Deployment (East US, approximate)</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Component</th><th>Spec</th><th>Est. Monthly Cost</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Controller VMs</td><td>2 × Standard_D2s_v3</td><td>~$140</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Agent VMSS</td><td>4 × Standard_F8s_v2</td><td>~$1,120</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Azure DB PostgreSQL</td><td>Standard_D2ds_v4, Zone-redundant</td><td>~$210</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Load Balancer</td><td>Standard (zone-redundant)</td><td>~$25</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Azure Files</td><td>1 TB ZRS</td><td>~$75</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Public IPs</td><td>3 static</td><td>~$11</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Data transfer</td><td>variable</td><td>~$35</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td></td><td><strong>~$1,616/mo</strong></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>Use Azure Spot VMs for agents by setting <code>agent_use_spot = true</code> to reduce agent costs by up to 80%.</p>

  <h2>Scale Agents</h2>
  <pre><code># Scale out agent VMSS immediately (overrides autoscale)
az vmss scale \
  --resource-group encodeswarmr-rg \
  --name encodeswarmr-agents \
  --new-capacity 6

# Or via Terraform
terraform apply -var="agent_desired_count=6"</code></pre>

  <h2>Cleanup</h2>
  <pre><code># Destroy all resources in the resource group
terraform destroy

# Alternatively, delete the resource group directly (faster)
az group delete --name encodeswarmr-rg --yes --no-wait</code></pre>

  <h2>File Reference</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>File</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>main.tf</code></td><td>Root module — calls sub-modules and sets providers</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>variables.tf</code></td><td>All input variable declarations with defaults</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>outputs.tf</code></td><td>Load balancer IP, controller IP, FQDN, etc.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>terraform.tfvars.example</code></td><td>Example values — copy to <code>terraform.tfvars</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/network/</code></td><td>VNet, subnets, NSGs, public IPs</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/controller/</code></td><td>Controller VM(s), managed disks, NIC, availability zone</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/agents/</code></td><td>VMSS, autoscale settings, custom script extension</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/database/</code></td><td>Azure DB for PostgreSQL Flexible Server</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/storage/</code></td><td>Storage account, Azure Files share, mount configuration</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/lb/</code></td><td>Azure Load Balancer, backend pools, health probes, rules</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
